      "writtenOn": "2019-04-22T15:05:29Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "CodeViewRecordElf isn’t really right, nor is it really descriptive enough. It’s just an arbitrary-length byte-oriented build ID. In ELF terminology, it’s just called a “build ID” so this should be either BuildID or, if you must, ELFBuildID.\n\nBut I think this would be usable for more than just ELF: we may want to transition Mach-O to use it too. So I’d be in favor of the more generic naming.",
